===Chile===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Chile}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal and regulated<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels illegal<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|prostitution in Chile}}

Adult prostitution is legal, subject to regulation, but related activities such as keeping brothels and pimping are prohibited.<ref name="procon" /><ref name="spl" /><ref name=report>[https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2006/78884.htm Report on Human Rights Practices 2006: Chile]. [[United States]] [[Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor]] (March 6, 2007). ''This article incorporates text from this source, which is in the [[public domain]].''</ref> Several hundred women were registered as prostitutes with the National Health Service,<ref name=report/> and undergo mandatory medical examinations.<ref name="spl" />

Although illegal, brothels are set up in the more remote areas of [[Chile]] in ports, mining towns, logging areas or anywhere where there are men working away from home.<ref name="escape">{{cite web|last1=Cotton|first1=John|title=Quasi-Legalized Prostitution in Chile|url=http://escapeamericanow.info/legalized-prostitution-in-chile/|website=Escape America Now|accessdate=5 December 2017|date=9 November 2008}}</ref>
{{clear}}

===Colombia===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Colombia}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal and regulated in brothels in designated tolerance zones<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels legal in designated tolerance zones<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|prostitution in Colombia}}

Prostitution is legal, regulated and limited to brothels in designated "tolerance zones".<ref name="statecol">{{cite web|url=https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2008/wha/119153.htm |title=2008 Human Rights Reports: Colombia |website=State.gov |date= |accessdate=2016-07-29}}</ref><ref name="nydailynews">{{cite web|last1=LeMire|first1=Jonathan|title=Secret service sex scandal: Prostitution is big business in Colombia|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/secret-service-sex-scandal-prostitution-big-business-colombia-article-1.1061734|website=NY Daily News|accessdate=22 April 2018|date=14 April 2012}}</ref> Sex workers are required to regular health checks.<ref name="spl" /> However the laws are rarely applied and prostitution is widespread,<ref name="nydailynews" /> partly due to poverty and internal displacement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.state.gov/j/drl/rls/hrrpt/2008/wha/119153.htm |title=2008 Human Rights Reports: Colombia |website=State.gov |date= |accessdate=2016-07-29}}</ref>

Domestically, [[organized crime]] networks, some related to illegal armed groups, are responsible for [[human trafficking]] for [[sexual slavery]] and the armed conflict has made a large number of internal trafficking victims vulnerable.<ref name="statecol"/>

[[UNAIDS]] estimate there to be 7,218 prostitutes in the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Colombia 2016 Country Factsheet|url=http://www.unaids.org/en/regionscountries/countries/colombia/|website=UNAIDS|accessdate=22 April 2018|language=en}}</ref>
{{clear}}

===Ecuador===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Ecuador}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal by registered prostitutes in licensed brothels<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels legal and regulated<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|prostitution in Ecuador}}

Prostitution is legal and regulated, as long as the prostitute is over the age of 18,<ref name="spl" /> registered, and works from a licensed brothel.<ref name="spl" /> Prostitution is widespread throughout the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyemerald.com/2007/07/16/ecuadorian-brothels-illuminate-red-light-truths/|title=Ecuadorian brothels illuminate red-light truths|first=Daily|last=Emerald|date=16 July 2007|publisher=|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ORuJAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA60&lpg=PA60&dq=Prostitution%20in%20Ecuador#v=onepage&q=Prostitution%20in%20Ecuador&f=false|title=CultureShock! Ecuador: A Survival Guide to Customs and Etiquette|first=Nicholas|last=Crowder|date=15 October 2009|publisher=Marshall Cavendish International Asia Pte Ltd|accessdate=9 January 2017|via=Google Books|isbn=9789814435734}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bigthink.com/dollars-and-sex/the-price-of-sex-in-south-america-a-guide-for-secret-service-agents|title=The Price of Sex in South America: A Guide for Secret Service Agents|first=Marina|last=Adshade|publisher=|accessdate=9 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=w5vSDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA333&lpg=PA333&dq=Prostitution%20in%20Ecuador#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Oxford Handbook of the Economics of Prostitution|first1=Scott|last1=Cunningham|first2=Manisha|last2=Shah|date=10 August 2016|publisher=Oxford University Press|accessdate=9 January 2017|via=Google Books|isbn=9780199915255}}</ref> Many brothels and prostitutes operate outside the regulatory system and the regulations have been less strictly enforced in recent years.<ref name="spl" /> 25,000 prostitutes were registered in the year 2,000.<ref name="soguel2">{{cite web|last1=Soguel|first1=Dominique|title=Ecuador Sex Workers Target HIV-AIDS Prevention|url=http://womensenews.org/2009/04/ecuador-sex-workers-target-hiv-aids-prevention/|website=Women's eNews|accessdate=27 December 2017|date=10 April 2009}}</ref> In 2007 it was estimated that 70% of the prostitutes in the country were from [[Colombia]].<ref name="crowder">{{cite book|last1=Crowder|first1=Nicholas|title=Culture shock!. a survival guide to customs and etiquette|date=2006|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|location=Tarrytown, NY|isbn=978-0761424956}}</ref> The country attracts Colombian prostitutes as the currency is the [[United States dollar|US$]] rather than the unstable [[Colombian peso]].<ref name="soguel2" />

[[Quito]] was the first city in Ecuador to regulate prostitution in 1921, requiring prostitutes to be tested weekly for [[Sexually transmitted infections|STIs]] and the results recorded in the "Register of Venereal Disease". Testing and any necessary treatment was free to the prostitutes.<ref name="anthro">{{cite web|title=Quito: History and Prostitution|url=http://andesanthropologist.blogspot.co.uk/2011/03/quito-history-and-prostitution.html|website=Andes Anthropologist|accessdate=27 December 2017 |date = 30 March 2011}}</ref> [[Guayaquil]] and [[Riobamba]] introduced a similar system of regulation in 1925.<ref name="anthro" /> In 1939, about 1,000 prostitutes were registered in Quito.<ref name="anthro" />
{{clear}}

===Falkland Islands===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Falkland Islands}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels illegal<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|Prostitution in the British Overseas Territories#Falkland Islands}}
Prostitution in the [[Falkland Islands]] is legal but related activities such as solicitation and keeping a brothel are prohibited by the Crimes Ordinance 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Crimes Ordinance 2014|url=https://www.legislation.gov.fk/download/pdf/6c9c7e4a-a076-4a64-a48e-7143f8926b44/eb16e7a2-f7c9-41b2-963e-c0349baff69a/fiord-2014-13_2017-07-31.pdf|website=Falklands Islands Government|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref> A man compelling his wife to become a prostitute is a grounds for divorce under the Matrimonial Proceedings (Summary Jurisdiction) Ordinance 1967.<ref>{{cite web|title=Matrimonial Proceedings (Summary Jurisdiction) Ordinance 1967|url=https://www.legislation.gov.fk/download/pdf/d42c55f8-fefd-40bb-8fa7-3eda37e18b5f/1ce39e47-7025-4e1f-8a5a-4bae192a59f1/fiord-1967-10_2017-07-31.pdf|website=Government of the Falkland Islands|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref> Soldiers returning from tours on the islands report little or no prostitution in the Falkland Islands.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sex and the Falkland Islands|url=https://www.arrse.co.uk/community/threads/sex-and-the-falkland-islands.177228/|website=Army Rumour Service|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref>
