===Paraguay===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Paraguay}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels illegal<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|prostitution in Paraguay}}

Prostitution is legal for persons over the age of 18,<ref>[https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2005/61737.htm Paraguay]. State.gov (2006-03-08). Retrieved on 2011-03-30.</ref> but related activities such as brothel keeping are prohibited.<ref name="procon" /> Prostitution is common in the country. Brothels are also common, even some rural villages have a small bar/brothel on the outskirts.<ref name="kopczinski" />

Whilst there is no red-light district in the capital, [[Asunción]], street prostitution is widespread in the city centre, especially around Plaza Uruguaya.<ref name="points">{{cite web|title=Scam City: Asuncion Paraguay|url=http://first2board.com/pointssummary/2014/10/28/scam-city-asuncion-paraguay-edition/|website=Points Summary|accessdate=30 December 2017|date=28 October 2014}}</ref> Brothels are also common in the city centre.<ref name="points" /> Prostitutes can also be found in bars and discos.<ref name="kopczinski">{{cite web|last1=Kopczinski|first1=H.W.|title=Domizilland Paraguay|url=http://paraguay-online.net/alltag/prostitution.html|website=Paraguay Online|accessdate=30 December 2017|language=German}}</ref>
