===Peru===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Peru}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal and regulated<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels legal and regulated
}}
{{main|prostitution in Peru}}

Prostitution between adults is legal for women and men over 18 years of age if they register with municipal authorities and carry a health certificate.<ref name="autoperu">{{cite web |url= https://www.state.gov/g/drl/rls/hrrpt/2008/wha/119170.htm |title= 2008 Human Rights Report: Peru|accessdate=2007-11-29 |website= US Department of State |publisher= |date= }}</ref> [[Brothels]] must be licensed. The vast majority of prostitutes work in the [[informal sector]], where they lack health protection.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=6WYZ0wNpZfIC&pg=PA179&dq=Prostitution%20in%20Peru#v=onepage&q=Prostitution%20in%20Peru&f=false|title=Men who Sell Sex: International Perspectives on Male Prostitution and HIV/AIDS|first=Peter|last=Aggleton|date=1 January 1999|publisher=Temple University Press|accessdate=9 January 2017|via=Google Books|isbn=9781566396691}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-5WyPfynlwMC&pg=PA518&dq=Prostitution%20in%20Peru#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Encyclopedia of Prostitution and Sex Work|first=Melissa Hope|last=Ditmore|date=1 January 2006|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|accessdate=9 January 2017|via=Google Books|isbn=9780313329708}}</ref><ref name="autoperu"/> Individual police officers tolerate the operation of unlicensed brothels.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.unhcr.org/refworld/publisher,USDOS,,PER,484f9a3528,0.html |title= Trafficking in Persons Report 2008 - Peru|accessdate=2009-11-16 |website= The UN Refugee Agency |publisher= |date= }}</ref>
