===Saint Lucia===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Saint Lucia}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution illegal<br>Buying sex legal
}}
Prostitution is illegal but tolerated.<ref name="procon">{{cite web|title=100 Countries and Their Prostitution Policies|url=https://prostitution.procon.org/view.resource.php?resourceID=000772|website=ProCon|accessdate=22 December 2017}}</ref> Prostitution laws are rarely enforced.<ref name="chartsbin" /> There are reports that strip clubs are used as fronts for prostitution, and that some are owned, or protected by corrupt police officials.<ref name="chartsbin" />

The country is a destination for [[female sex tourism]].<ref name="indi"/>

[[Sex trafficking]]<ref name="sextour" /> and [[child prostitution]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Authorities Worried Over The Increase Of Child Prostitution In St. Lucia|url=http://pridenews.ca/2013/09/17/authorities-worried-over-the-increase-of-child-prostitution-in-st-lucia/|website=Pride News|accessdate=21 April 2018|date=17 September 2013}}</ref> are problems in the country.
{{clear}}

===Saint Martin===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Saint Martin}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution legal<br>Buying sex legal<br>Brothels illegal<br>Procuring illegal<br>Solicitation illegal
}}
{{main|Prostitution in Overseas France#Saint Martin}}
The growth of tourism starting in the 1970s caused an increase in prostitution in [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]].<ref name="benoit">{{Cite journal|last1=Benoit|first1=Catherine|title=Sex, AIDS, migration, and prostitution : human trafficking in the Caribbean|journal=New West Indian Guide / Nieuwe West-Indische Gids|volume=73|issue=3–4|pages=27–42|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/41125715|accessdate=30 December 2017|doi=10.1163/13822373-90002576|date=1 July 1999}}</ref> Although outlawed in 1946 by the "Loi de Marthe Richard", brothels were tolerated until the introduction of the new Penal code in 1991.<ref name="benoit" /> One hotel, now closed, was reserved fot French civil servants and reputedly offered the guests European prostitutes.<ref name="benoit" />

Despite laws prohibiting soliciting, street prostitution still exists, especially in the [[Quartier-d'Orleans]].<ref name="devin">{{cite web|last1=Le Devin|first1=Willy|title=Saint-Martin : une île, plusieurs mondes|url=http://www.liberation.fr/france/2017/09/15/saint-martin-une-ile-plusieurs-mondes_1596738|website=Libération|accessdate=30 December 2017|language=fr|date=15 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=France's hurricane-hit St Martin on guard for health threats|url=http://www.terradaily.com/reports/Frances_hurricane-hit_St_Martin_on_guard_for_health_threats_999.html|website=Terra Daily|accessdate=30 December 2017|date=16 September 2017}}</ref>
{{clear}}

