===Trinidad and Tobago===
{{Infobox
 |abovestyle = background:#cfc;
 |subheaderstyle = align-left
 |above        = {{Flagu|Trinidad and Tobago}}
 |subheader    = Prostitution illegal<br>Buying sex legal
}}
{{main|Prostitution in Trinidad and Tobago}}
Prostitution in Trinidad and Tobago is illegal and related activities such as brothel keeping, soliciting and pimping are illegal.<ref name="spl"/>

In [[Trinidad]], [[Port of Spain]] is the main place of sex work,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbean360.com/news/trinidad_tobago_news/women-trafficked-for-prostitution-and-forced-marriage-in-trinidad|title=Women trafficked for prostitution and forced marriage in Trinidad - Caribbean360|date=24 January 2014|publisher=|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipsnews.net/1996/02/trinidad-and-tobago-child-prostitution-is-a-thriving-business/|title=Trinidad and Tobago: Child Prostitution Is A Thriving Business - Inter Press Service|publisher=|accessdate=11 January 2017}}</ref> including street prostitution on Roberts and Murray Streets.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brown|first1=John|title=What about street prostitutes, Louis?|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/letters/2011/02/14/what-about-street-prostitutes-louis|website=The Trinidad Guardian Newspaper|accessdate=4 January 2018|date=15 February 2011}}</ref> New [[brothels]] continue to open across the country, particularly in the south where they are incorporated into small bars and rum shops and are difficult to detect, and in central, where they operate out of a normal-looking flats in a neighbourhood.<ref>{{cite web|title=Trinidad and Tobago 2016 Trafficking in Persons Report|url=https://www.state.gov/j/tip/rls/tiprpt/countries/2016/258880.htm|website=U.S. Department of State|accessdate=3 January 2018}}</ref> Many of the sex workers come from Colombia, Venezuela and Cuba. Some regularly commute between their home nation and Trinidad.<ref name="pope">{{cite book|last1=Pope|first1=Cynthia|last2=White,|first2=Renée T.|last3=Malow|first3=Robert|title=HIV/AIDS : global frontiers in prevention/intervention|date=2009|publisher=Routledge|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0415953832}}</ref>

Prostitution in less common in [[Tobago]], some prostitutes from Trinidad move to Tobago for the tourist season.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fido|first1=Austin|title=The shady side of paradise|url=http://www.guardian.co.tt/entertainment/2015-09-20/shady-side-paradise|website=Trinidad & Tobago Guardian|accessdate=23 December 2017|date=20 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Gibbings|first1=Wesley|title=The High Cost of Sex Tourism|url=http://www.ipsnews.net/1997/03/trinidad-and-tobago-health-the-high-cost-of-sex-tourism/|website=IPS News|accessdate=4 January 2018|date=24 March 1997}}</ref>
{{clear}}

